For sale is my 581-Series Ruger Mini 14 Tactical. I purchased this back in September (took receipt of it 9/11/12). It has functioned flawlessly and has been well-cared for. It has been kept in a locked cabinet when not in use and has always been transported in a padded rifle case. It has never been dropped or damaged in any way. There are some slight marks on the stock from normal use, but the metal is clean and rust-free, as it should be. I have fired about 350 rounds (.223 and 5.56, both brass and steel) through this rifle without a single failure of any kind.

This rifle is the 16.5" Tactical model in a Hogue Overmolded Stock (I have the original synthetic stock as well and will include it). I have 3 20-round Ruger Magazines for this rifle as well as the standard 5-round Ruger Magazine. I have a Redfield 2-7x Scope mounted in Warne QD Rings on the rifle which are also included. I do not have the original Ruger rings that came with this rifle as I sold them to help fund the Warne Rings (which are far superior, in my opinion). I also have the Warne Torx tool for achieving optimal torque on the rings (25 in/lbs., I believe). All of this will be included in the original boxes (the box for the rifle is slightly worn and the box for the scope is missing the barcode because I redeemed a rebate on it). 

I am offering this up as a package deal and will not split it up. the included image is of the actual rifle for sale. I took it a couple of months ago. I will be happy to send photos of the other two 20-round magazines and the 5-round magazine if you would like to see them prior to purchase, but I can assure you they are there. 

This rifle is for sale in the Columbia area (I live in Sumter). I am willing to drive a short distance to meet you to make the transaction. I will fill out a bill of sale with the details about the rifle (serial number, model number, etc.) as well as my name, address, phone number and DL number and I expect the same information from you (I will accept a CWP in lieu of a DL). title: Want To Buy:  The Minnesota Legislature will convene tomorrow (ACT NOW)
postcontent:
Dear GOCRA supporters,

 The Minnesota Legislature will convene tomorrow, and given the media coverage of recent events, there is little doubt that gun control will be on the agenda of many metro legislators.

The threats we face
 With Mark Dayton in the Governor's mansion and DFL majorities in both the House and the Senate, that poses a real and significant threat.  The House Public Safety Finance and Policy Committee is chaired by Rep. Michael Paymar (DFL, 64B, St. Paul), who has been a leading voice in destroying your rights.

 In the Senate, the Transportation and Public Safety Committee will be led by Sen. Scott Dibble (DFL, 61, Minneapolis). We expect him to attempt a so-called "assault weapon" ban, and Sen. John Marty (DFL, 66, Roseville) is already pushing licensing and registration of your legally owned guns.

Our secret weapon
 Things look dire, but we have a secret weapon: you.

 The gun control "movement" isn't grass-roots: it's Astroturf. A tiny minority of misguided, zealots, funded by the deep pockets of limousine liberals and foundations, make a lot of noise, but have no real popular support.

 On the other hand, the gun rights community is real, large, and engaged. That will be vital in the coming days and weeks.

What you can do
 •Call your Minnesota senator and representative today! Their info at the bottom of this email. If it's missing, you haven't told us where you live. That's vital information when we need to make sure that certain representatives hear from their gun-owning constituents. Please click the link and give us your address, so we can get your help when needed most.

•Email your Minnesota senator and representative.  Your message should be short, polite, and in your own words: ◦ I'm a constituent
◦ I'm a law-abiding gun owner
◦ I oppose ANY new restrictions on my freedoms
◦ The legislature should deal with the criminals and the insane, but not blame or punish us for their actions
◦ I support the Gun Owners Civil Rights Alliance and their mission (and you should, too!)
◦ Forward this email to your friends and family! Encourage them to sign up for these emails. Together, we are powerful.


•Send a donation! For the last 23 years, we've run on a shoestring, and many activists have paid with their own wealth, careers and family time to support, defend and advance your rights. With the threats we face today, a pure volunteer effort may not be enough. Any amount you can spare -- $50, $25, even $10 will help. Think about this: If every carry permit holder sent us a dollar a year, we'd have a full-time attorney working for your rights. If every gun owner sent us a buck a year, we'd have a busy staff working full time for you.

Still have energy? Great! We need it!
 • Write a letter to the editor of your local paper. In 100 words or less, tell them that as a law-abiding gun owner, you should not be blamed or punished for the actions of criminals and crazies.

Stay tuned; we'll have more news in the coming days, and some exciting opportunities.
